<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1058,1035,1087]" pageId="26" pageNumber="985">
E t y m o l o g y: The trivial name, 
<emphasis box="[569,666,1035,1056]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="985">imparilus</emphasis>
, is a Latin adjective derived from 
<emphasis box="[151,242,1065,1086]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="985">imparilis</emphasis>
(= unequal); with reference to the sex-dimorphic condition of the antenna.
</paragraph>
